Three men have been arrested in connecton wtih the aggravated burglary of 73-year-old Sligo pensioner Tom Niland. The men were arrested on suspicion of the burglary in Skreen, Co Sligo on January 18th. The men are aged in their 50s, 30s and 20s and are currently detained under Section 4 of the Criminal Justice Act 1984 at separate Garda stations in the Sligo and Leitrim division. Mr Niland was hospitalised and on life support following the burglary. Mr Niland was attacked at his home on the Sligo to Ballina road by a gang of masked men who called to the door at about 7pm on January 18th. The bachelor, who farmed from his mid-teens until his retirement seven years ago, was watching television alone at the time.